Use case:  I use Confluence OnDemand like a vast work process documentation system for my enterprise.  I have ten or twenty confluence pages open in tabs within my browser at all times.  And at any given time, several of those tabs are in edit mode.

Problem: often I will leave work without remembering to traverse the whole tree to exit edit mode for all open pages.  When I get to a new work location, I will be faced with a large number of "previous draft" messages, and sometimes not knowing for sure if this condition (unclosed edit mode pages) may exist on more than one machine.

Resolution/feature request: automatically render the favicon for any page in edit mode in red.  Or, since we can customize favicons, allow us to provide two.  Or just color the background.  Some way to quickly and easily see which pages are vulnerable.

